title: For Sale:   Classic Old Commie Gun CZ50 service quality Walther PPK clone 32acp w/1 mag
postcontent: The design of this pistol was clearly inspired by the Walther PPK. Unlike most "copies", many experts believe this version was in-fact a better gun then the one that inspired it. Very well built and durable design. Excellent grips. Feels good in the hand, with smooth trigger.One of the worlds best enduring conceal carry firearms. Until the 1980s most European law enforcement used the .32acp round as the standard cartridge.  Very good mechanics and bore. Finish is pretty much shot.  Would be an excellent gun to refinish or just to use for conceal carry.  Doesn't really have pitting or rust.  Finish looks like it flaked off off (suspect bad cosmoline). Needs to be cleaned in and out before range time.   More pleasent to shoot, and much less recoil than 9mm or .380acp, yet readily available. Small enough for most purses/bags. The Vz.50 (commercially sold as Cz-50) is an all steel semi-automatic pistol made in Czechoslovakia. It is chambered in the plentiful 7.65mm ( .32 A.C.P. ) caliber. It has a simple blowback action with a fixed barrel. The trigger is traditional double-action, with an exposed hammer and a frame-mounted decocking safety lever. The sights are fixed and the magazine is single stacked with a capacity of 8 rounds. The magazine release button is located relatively high on the left side of the frame, behind the trigger.
